  "texts": [
    "The signature contains the sorts, function signatures, and grammar of this cognitive calculus, presented in a manner that is standard and self-explanatory for the most part.",
    "As obvious, lower-case Greek letters are formulae, bolded majuscule Roman letters are intensional/modal operators (K for knows, B for believes, I for intends, etc.).",
    "Perceives, Knows, Says, Common-knowledge Believes, Desires, Intends, Ought-to",
    "Next is the standard set of inference schemata for DCEC.",
    "They say that when what is above the vertical line is instantiated, that which is below can be inferred (in accordance with that instantiation); this top-bottom notation is common in descriptions of so-called natural deduction."
  ],
